phase2.explanation:
Trying to load data that doesn't exist results in `null`.

**The fix:**
```csharp
if (PlayerPrefs.HasKey("GameSave"))
{
    string json = PlayerPrefs.GetString("GameSave");
    GameState state = JsonUtility.FromJson<GameState>(json);
    if (state != null)
    {
        Debug.Log("Loaded!");
    }
}
else
{
    Debug.Log("No save data found!");
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if data exists before loading."
